<topic id = "AENBP70A1406036008">
<title>
Ring groove clearance
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Before checking, piston grooves must be clean, dry and free from carbon deposits.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fit new piston ring (1) into piston groove, and measure clearance between ring and ring land using feeler gauge (2). If clearance is out of limit, replace piston.
</ptxt>
